
# ğŸ”· Cisco EIGRP Protocol Configuration Guide

This README outlines a basic setup for EIGRP (Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol).

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Basic Router Setup

```bash
enable
configure terminal
hostname ROUTER_NAME
no ip domain-lookup
```

---

## ğŸŒ Interface IP Configuration

```bash
interface FastEthernet0/0
  ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit

interface FastEthernet0/1
  ip address 10.0.0.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” EIGRP Configuration

```bash
router eigrp 100
  network 192.168.1.0
  network 10.0.0.0
  no auto-summary
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” Verification Commands

```bash
show ip protocols
show ip eigrp neighbors
show ip route eigrp
show running-config
```

---

## ğŸ’¾ Save Configuration

```bash
copy running-config startup-config
```

---

## ğŸ§  Notes

- EIGRP is a hybrid protocol (distance-vector with some link-state features).
- Uses DUAL algorithm for route selection.
- Use `no auto-summary` to avoid classful routing behavior.

